vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 6
  }
}
title: |md
  # EOI (End of Interrupt) Decision Tree
  After IRQ Handler Completion
| {near: top-center}
start: "IRQ Handler Returns" {
  shape: oval
  style.fill: "#E8F5E9"
  style.stroke: "#2E7D32"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}
check_irq: "IRQ Number?" {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#FFF3E0"
  style.stroke: "#E65100"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}
master_only: "Send EOI to Master PIC\noutb(0x20, 0x20)" {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#BBDEFB"
  style.stroke: "#1565C0"
}
both_pics: "Send EOI to Both PICs" {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#C8E6C9"
  style.stroke: "#2E7D32"
}
slave_eoi: "1. Slave EOI\noutb(0xA0, 0x20)" {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#DCEDC8"
  style.stroke: "#558B2F"
}
master_eoi: "2. Master EOI\noutb(0x20, 0x20)" {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#DCEDC8"
  style.stroke: "#558B2F"
}
pic_ready: "PIC Ready for\nNext Interrupt" {
  shape: oval
  style.fill: "#C8E6C9"
  style.stroke: "#1B5E20"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}
no_eoi: "EOI Forgotten!" {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#FFCDD2"
  style.stroke: "#C62828"
  style.font-color: "#B71C1C"
  style.bold: true
}
pic_blocked: "PIC ISR Bit Still Set\nInterrupts BLOCKED" {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#FFCDD2"
  style.stroke: "#C62828"
}
system_hang: "System Appears Hung\n- No Timer Ticks\n- No Keyboard\n- No Future IRQs" {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#EF9A9A"
  style.stroke: "#B71C1C"
  style.font-color: "#B71C1C"
}
irq_range: |md
  **IRQ Range Reference:**
  - IRQ 0-7: Master PIC only
  - IRQ 8-15: Slave PIC (cascaded via IRQ2)
  **Port Addresses:**
  - Master CMD: 0x20
  - Slave CMD: 0xA0
  - EOI Command: 0x20
| {
  near: top-right
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#F5F5F5"
  style.stroke: "#9E9E9E"
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
start -> check_irq
check_irq -> master_only: "IRQ 0-7\n(Timer, Keyboard,\nCascade, etc.)"
check_irq -> both_pics: "IRQ 8-15\n(RTC, Mouse,\nDisk, etc.)"
both_pics -> slave_eoi
slave_eoi -> master_eoi
master_eoi -> pic_ready
master_only -> pic_ready
no_eoi -> pic_blocked
pic_blocked -> system_hang
check_irq -> no_eoi: "Forgot EOI\n(Common Bug!)"
legend: {
  near: bottom-center
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#FAFAFA"
  style.stroke: "#BDBDBD"
  correct: "Correct Path" {
    style.fill: "#C8E6C9"
    shape: rectangle
  }
  error: "Error Path" {
    style.fill: "#FFCDD2"
    shape: rectangle
  }
  correct -> error: {style.opacity: 0}
}
why_both: |md
  **Why Send EOI to Both?**
  Slave PIC's INT output is connected
  to Master PIC's IRQ2 line.
  When IRQ8-15 fires:
  1. Slave sets its ISR bit
  2. Slave signals Master via IRQ2
  3. Master sets its ISR bit for IRQ2
  Clearing both ISR bits is required
  for future interrupts to be delivered.
| {
  near: bottom-right
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#E3F2FD"
  style.stroke: "#1976D2"
}